  "intent_precise": "TG Nextera XT index kit v2 Set A to D: Using thermocycler_plate (pcr_plate, slot 2), temp_rack (labware, slot 4), mag_plate (pcr_plate, slot 6), DNA_plate (pcr_plate, slot 2). With thermocycler module, temperature module, magnetic module. (1) Open thermocycler lid. (2) Set temperature to 4\u00b0C. (3) Disengage magnets to release beads. (4) Pause: format (5) Transfer 2\u00b5L from source (A1, A1) to destination (A1, A1). (6) Pause: Switch DNA plate out with Primer plate (7) Transfer 2\u00b5L from source A1 to destination A1. (8) Close thermocycler lid. (9) Operate thermocycler. (10) Run thermocycler profile for 1 cycles. (11) Open thermocycler lid. (12) Pause: Move thermocycler plate to magdeck.\n    Replace DNA plate with indexing plate I.\n    Replace thermocycler plate with reaction plate C (13) Transfer 45\u00b5L from source A1 to destination A1. (14) Incubate for 5 minutes. (15) Engage magnets for bead separation. (16) Incubate for 10 minutes. (17) Distribute 10\u00b5L from source A1 to destination wells A1-A1 (4 wells). (18) Incubate for 6 minutes. (19) Disengage magnets to release beads. (20) Transfer 40\u00b5L from source A1 to destination A1. (21) Incubate for 2 minutes. (22) Engage magnets for bead separation. (23) Incubate for 3 minutes. (24) Distribute 2\u00b5L from source A1 to destination wells A1-A1 (5 wells). (25) Close thermocycler lid. (26) Operate thermocycler. (27) Run thermocycler profile for 1 cycles. (28) Open thermocycler lid. (29) Pause: Move thermocycler plate to magdeck.\n        Replace indexing I plate with output plate.",
  "intent_concise": "Perform 2 distribution steps, magnetic bead separation, temperature control (4\u00b0C), thermocycling. (volumes 2\u00b5L-200\u00b5L, ~27 min total)",
  "intent": "For the TG Nextera XT index kit v2 Set A to D protocol, start by opening the thermocycler lid and setting the temperature module to 4\u00b0C, then disengage the magnets on the magnetic module and transfer 2\u00b5L from well A1 to A1 on both the DNA plate and primer plate before running one thermocycler cycle. After the thermocycler run, move the plate to the magnetic deck, add 45\u00b5L to well A1, and perform a series of magnetic bead separations with specific incubation times: 5 minutes before engaging magnets, 10 minutes with magnets engaged, then distribute 10\u00b5L to 4 wells and incubate 6 minutes before releasing beads again. Continue with a 40\u00b5L transfer, 2-minute incubation, another magnetic separation with 3-minute incubation, distribute 2\u00b5L to 5 wells, then run a final thermocycler cycle before moving the plate back to the magnetic deck and replacing the indexing plate with the output plate.",
